Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}, for the pasta. 
Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. 
Season @Beef Sizzler Steaks{4} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When hot, add the steaks and cook for ~{45%seconds} each side, until golden brown.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Wrap the steaks in #foil{} to keep warm and keep the pan to one side.

Add the @Fresh Tagliatelle{1} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes} 
then drain well. Pop the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, @Wild Mushroom Paste{1}, 
@Water for the Sauce{150%ml} and half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} 
into the now empty frying pan over medium heat with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. 
Bring to a simmer over medium heat, and once simmering, add the @Baby Spinach{125%g} 
a handful at a time until it has all wilted, about ~{2-3%minutes}.

Drain the pasta in a #colander{}, add to the sauce and mix well. Thinly slice the 
steaks. Divide the pasta between plates and top with the steaks. Sprinkle with 
the remaining hard cheese and snip over the @Chives{1%sprig} using #scissors{}. 
Enjoy!